org.universAAL.ontology.location

Class Place

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.universAAL.middleware.rdf.Resource
      • org.universAAL.middleware.rdf.FinalizedResource
        • org.universAAL.middleware.owl.ManagedIndividual

                • org.universAAL.ontology.location.Place
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IndoorPlace, OutdoorPlace, Space, Way

    public class Place
extends Location
    Ontological representation of a place (which is not only a location but also has some more properties. It is more concrete). Methods included in this class are the mandatory ones for representing an ontological concept in Java classes for universAAL. Usually it includes getters and setters for most of its properties.
    Author:
    chwirth
